# Supabase (CRITICAL — incorrect patterns BREAK auth in production)

## 🚨 Forbidden patterns (will break the app)

❌ `import { createMiddlewareClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'`
❌ `import { createClientComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'`
❌ Cookie methods named `get`, `set`, `remove`
❌ `await supabase.auth.getSession()` for authorization
❌ Any `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` use in a Client Component or `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` var

## ✅ Required patterns

- ALWAYS import from `@supabase/ssr`.
- ALWAYS use ONLY `getAll` / `setAll` cookie methods.
- ALWAYS use `await supabase.auth.getUser()` for authorization checks.

## Three client factories live in `lib/supabase/`

- `client.ts` — `createBrowserClient(...)` for Client Components.
- `server.ts` — `createServerClient(...)` with `cookies()` from
  `next/headers`. Wrap `cookieStore.set` in try/catch; Server Components can't
  set cookies, that's expected.
- `middleware.ts` — `createServerClient(...)` reading from
  `request.cookies`, writing to `supabaseResponse.cookies`.
  IMMEDIATELY call `await supabase.auth.getUser()` after creating the client.
  DO NOT put any code between client creation and `getUser()`.
  RETURN `supabaseResponse` as-is, OR copy `supabaseResponse.cookies.getAll()`
  onto any new response. Otherwise cookies desync and users log out randomly.

## RLS

- Every table in `public` MUST have RLS enabled and explicit policies for each
  of SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE separately. Never `FOR ALL`.
- Always specify `TO authenticated` or `TO anon` — never default.
- Use `auth.uid()` and `auth.jwt()` for user checks. NEVER trust
  `auth.jwt() -> 'user_metadata'` for authorization (user-mutable).
- Performance: index every column referenced in a policy. Wrap function calls
  as `(select auth.uid())` so Postgres caches them per statement.
- RLS migrations live in the SAME migration file as the table definition.

## Service-role client

- Constructed in a server-only module (`import 'server-only'` at top).
- Used only from Route Handlers / Server Actions / cron with their own
  authorization check already done.
- Never logged. Never embedded in URLs.

## Types and queries

- All clients typed with the Database generic once it's generated.
- Always destructure `{ data, error }` and check `error` before using `data`.
  Never `data!`.
- `.single()` for exactly-one, `.maybeSingle()` for zero-or-one.
- Prefer narrow `.select('id, name, ...')` over `.select('*')` for type narrowing.
- Multi-step writes: wrap in a Postgres function (RPC). Call via
  `supabase.rpc('fn_name', args)` — Supabase JS does not expose ad-hoc transactions.
